Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb} and @garlic{2%cloves}, keeping them separate. Finely chop @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), separating whites from greens.

== Ginger Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} (save the rest for serving) and a big pinch of ginger; cook, stirring frequently, until golden brown, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Spicy Mayo ==

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, ¼ tsp water, and @sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste.

== Okonomiyaki Fritters ==

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @eggs{2}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, and ¼ cup water.

Whisk in @tempura mix{82%g} until no lumps remain.

Fold in cabbage, garlic, scallion whites, and remaining ginger. Season with @salt{1/2%tsp} and @pepper{}. Mix thoroughly to combine, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when added to the pan, carefully add half the batter. Cook until browned and crispy, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> If fritter begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat.

Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

Repeat process with remaining batter to make 2 fritters total.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with salt and pepper to taste.

Divide ginger rice between plates. Cut okonomiyaki fritters into quarters and place atop rice. Top with sriracha mayo and @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon}. Garnish with scallion greens and remaining sesame seeds. Serve.